  "text": "Successfully implemented automatic .gitignore management for Rulesets project:\n\n**Architecture Overview:**\n- GitignoreManager class handles all gitignore operations\n- Integrated into runRulesetsV0 orchestration without breaking changes\n- Provider write methods now optionally return WriteResult with generated paths\n- Override files (.rulesekeep, .rulesetignore) provide user control\n\n**Key Files Created:**\n- packages/core/src/gitignore/types.ts - TypeScript interfaces\n- packages/core/src/gitignore/utils.ts - Path handling and parsing utilities  \n- packages/core/src/gitignore/GitignoreManager.ts - Main implementation\n- packages/core/src/gitignore/index.ts - Module exports\n- packages/core/src/gitignore/__tests__/ - Comprehensive test coverage\n- packages/core/src/gitignore/README.md - Documentation\n\n**Integration Points:**\n- Modified packages/types/src/destination-plugin.ts to add WriteResult interface\n- Updated CursorProvider and WindsurfProvider to return generated paths\n- Enhanced packages/core/src/index.ts orchestration to collect paths and update gitignore\n- Added exports for external usage\n\n**Testing Strategy:**\n- Unit tests for all utility functions (path normalization, pattern matching)\n- Comprehensive GitignoreManager class tests (happy path, errors, edge cases)\n- Integration tests with runRulesetsV0\n- Mocked filesystem operations for reliable test execution\n\n**User Experience:**\n- Automatic gitignore management with no configuration required\n- Override files for fine-grained control\n- Clear logging of what files were added/kept\n- Graceful error handling that doesn't break builds\n- Cross-platform path handling\n\nThe implementation successfully meets all requirements and provides a robust foundation for gitignore management in the Rulesets ecosystem.",
  "sections": [
    "Project Notes"
  ],
